        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(center)">3<hi rend="sup">rd</hi>
                <hi rend="indent(2)"><date>Aug 37</date></hi></p>
            <p rend="align(center)">
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
                <hi rend="indent(1)">
                    <date>Ab 22nd 5597</date>
                </hi>
            </p>
            <p>(<date>Aug. 23, 1837</date>)</p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Lewis Allen Esq.</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Parnass K.K.M.I.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir:</p>
            <p>Understanding that the <persName>Rev. Jacques Judah Lyons</persName>. Hazan<lb/> of a
                Congregation of Israelites in <placeName>Paramaribo, <sic>Surinan</sic> Dutch<lb/>
                    Guiana, South America</placeName>, is desirous of reading the Prayers<lb/> for
                an entire <date>Sabbath</date>, and you having submitted to my inspec-<lb/>tion his
                credentials, which prove that he has been Hazan for<lb/> a space of five years, and
                that his conduct has uniformly<lb/> been religious: I yield cheerfully to him the
                right of so<lb/> reading the entire service, I doing this however <sic>however</sic>
                I<lb/> utterly disclaim the power of the congregation, unless by a<lb/> majority in
                meeting <sic>ssembled</sic> of compelling the Hazan for the<lb/> time being, to
                admit any other person to officiate upon any<lb/> occasion, or for any purpose
                whatever, by yielding the right<lb/> of the Tebah to him is owing a mere spirit of
                courtesy, as<lb/> I could not well refuse one who has been in office, to read<lb/>
                the service, if he is earnestly desirous to do so; although I<lb/> must at the same
                time express my surprise at the unusual re-<lb/>quest, especially as no
                communication whatever from the appli-<lb/>cant himself has up to this moment
                reached me. In conversa-<lb/>tion with Sundry persons I express myself before
                    <persName>Mr. Lyons</persName><lb/> arrival, that if he had been Hazan, I would
                permit him to<lb/> read; I trust therefore that my compliance with the Revd.<lb/>
                gentleman's implied wishes may not be ascribed to motives<lb/> which I do not
                entertain.</p>
            <p rend="indent(7)">Yours respectfully</p>
            <p rend="indent(7)">(over)<persName role="author">Isaac Leeser</persName></p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>This follows signature</p>
            <p>This note is not private, you may therefore show it to<lb/> any one you please.</p>
            <p>Addr. <addressee>Lewis Allen Esq.</addressee>, Parnass K.K.M.I
                    <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
            <p>Note (on same page as address)</p>
            <p>
                <persName role="author">Revd I Leeser</persName>
                <date>22/37 Augt.</date>
                <placeName>Phila.</placeName>
            </p>
            <p>His permission to let <persName>Revd I Lyons</persName> to say <date>Saturday</date>
                prayers<lb/> do it out of Courtesy &amp;c. &amp;c. Can make this public—</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Enclosing my reply to the same.</p>
            <p>Dear Sir:</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">As you have taken the liberty to address a letter to me<lb/>
                explaining your motives for allowing the <persName>Revd. I. Lyons</persName> to<lb/>
                read prayers, which explanation I never asked for I take this<lb/> method to tell
                you I have neither time nor do I choose to make<lb/> your sentiments known to the
                Congregation.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">And the next time you address a letter to me I wish<lb/> first to
                read the contents</p>
            <p rend="indent(10)">I am Yours resp</p>
            <p>To <persName role="author">Revd. I. Leeser</persName></p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">(enclosed with the above letter)</p>
        </body>
